# Titanic Intel Integration Strategy

Modernizing the Workspace Dashboard with a specialized "Titanic Challenge" layer, allowing Mistral to execute Kaggle workflows directly through natural language.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This integration assumes that [titanic/train.csv](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/titanic/train.csv) and [test.csv](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/test.csv) are present in `~/Desktop/Istrazivanje/titanic/`.
> The [kaggle](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/tests/test_workspace_engine.py#196-223) CLI must be configured with an API token for submissions to work.

## Proposed Changes

### Dashboard Enhancements

#### [MODIFY] [workspace_dashboard.py](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/workspace_dashboard.py)
1. **New command**: [titanic](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/titanic) — Enters a specialized Titanic Challenge menu.
2. **Sub-commands**:
   - `train` — Runs CV on the selected feature version.
   - [submit](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/trinity_titanic_challenge/TITANIC_TRINITY_PROTOCOL.py#93-133) — Generates and uploads a submission to Kaggle.
   - `stats` — Shows the Trinity Knowledge Base (best scores, effectiveness).
3. **AI Upgrade**: 
   - Feed the [TitanicTrinityChallenge](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/trinity_titanic_challenge/TITANIC_TRINITY_PROTOCOL.py#51-179) feature engineering versions (v1-v4) into the Mistral `SYSTEM_PROMPT`.
   - Allow Mistral to map natural language requests like "Istreniraj mi v3 model" to the internal protocol.

